1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:07,110
My hat! My straw hat!

3
00:02:07,110 --> 00:02:08,730
It's right there.

4
00:02:08,730 --> 00:02:10,400
Huh? Oh, yeah. Here it is.

5
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,940
Rise and shine.

6
00:02:12,570 --> 00:02:14,320
Oh? Are those guys still...?

7
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:15,870
They left...

8
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:17,200
thanks to you.

9
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,330
Me?

10
00:02:18,330 --> 00:02:22,000
Gin said, "I'll see you again
on the Grand Line."

11
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:24,830
Gin said that...

12
00:02:25,330 --> 00:02:26,330
to you?

13
00:02:26,330 --> 00:02:27,840
He said it to you!

14
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:33,840
Speaking of which,
since I drove them off,

15
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,930
today is my last day
doing chores, right?

16
00:02:35,930 --> 00:02:37,050
Congrats.

17
00:02:37,390 --> 00:02:38,760
Which means that you'll...

18
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:40,520
...not be going with you!

19
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,180
I won't become a pirate.

20
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,690
I'll keep working here as a cook

21
00:02:44,690 --> 00:02:47,860
until I get that old fart
to acknowledge my skills.

22
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,320
I get it. I give up.

23
00:02:50,730 --> 00:02:52,820
Your hand hasn't given up yet!

24
00:02:56,740 --> 00:03:01,700
I can't leave here when every
last one of them is unreliable.

25
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:04,790
But... I am hoping
to head out someday...

26
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:07,080
to the Grand Line.

27
00:03:09,790 --> 00:03:11,550
Then let's go now.

28
00:03:11,550 --> 00:03:13,510
It's not the right time yet.

29
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:17,470
Hey...

30
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:20,220
have you heard of the All Blue?!

31
00:03:20,220 --> 00:03:21,350
Nope.

32
00:03:21,350 --> 00:03:23,600
You've seriously never heard of it?!

33
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,100
That sea itself is a miracle!

34
00:03:27,190 --> 00:03:28,400
In that sea...

35
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:31,610
The East Blue, West Blue,
North Blue, and South Blue...

36
00:03:31,610 --> 00:03:34,650
Fish from all four corners
of the world swim there!

37
00:03:37,110 --> 00:03:39,870
To us cooks, it's a dreamlike paradise!

38
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:43,450
I mean, that's the Grand Line
for you. So, you've never...?

39
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:50,920
He still lights up
when he talks about it...

40
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:53,920
What a goofball.

41
00:03:59,550 --> 00:04:02,140
Time to eat, guys!

42
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:04,100
Thank goodness...

43
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:05,600
We can finally eat!

44
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,350
Food! Food! Food!

45
00:04:13,270 --> 00:04:15,820
Hey, where are we supposed to sit?

46
00:04:15,820 --> 00:04:16,740
Where's our food?

47
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:19,160
Seats are all taken.

48
00:04:19,820 --> 00:04:21,370
Sit on the floor and eat.

49
00:04:21,370 --> 00:04:22,870
No seats?

50
00:04:22,870 --> 00:04:24,370
How is that even possible?!

51
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:26,660
This is a restaurant!

52
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:29,500
Well, whatever...

53
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:31,830
They're acting kinda weird...

54
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,000
What's new?

55
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:39,970
Hey! Who prepared
the soup this morning?!

56
00:04:40,550 --> 00:04:42,720
Hey, that was all me!
Pretty good, right?!

57
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,970
I took extra care in making it today!

58
00:04:45,470 --> 00:04:47,560
I can't eat a vile soup like this!

59
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,190
This is just slop!

60
00:04:56,440 --> 00:05:01,820
Hey... is human food not
to your liking, you damn tanuki?

61
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:05,030
It's an art to make
something this bad.

62
00:05:05,030 --> 00:05:06,740
It makes me sick to my stomach!

63
00:05:08,540 --> 00:05:11,210
Sorry, but I'd stake my
reputation on this soup.

64
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:14,000
You should go and get
your taste buds checked.

65
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,760
Ugh! This is disgusting!

66
00:05:22,430 --> 00:05:24,350
I can't eat it!

67
00:05:25,970 --> 00:05:26,810
Right, guys?!

68
00:05:28,020 --> 00:05:29,430
It's inedible!

69
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:32,770
This soup is revolting!

70
00:05:32,770 --> 00:05:34,310
I can't eat soup like this!

71
00:05:34,310 --> 00:05:36,770
This is terrible! Someone,
give me some water!

72
00:05:36,770 --> 00:05:39,150
Who are you bastards trying to fool?!

73
00:05:39,150 --> 00:05:42,410
You're a sham of a sous-chef,
just so you know.

74
00:05:42,410 --> 00:05:44,030
You've gotten stale!

75
00:05:44,030 --> 00:05:47,410
We're tired of you solving
every problem with your feet.

76
00:05:47,410 --> 00:05:50,120
If the food's bad,
we'll tell you it's bad!

77
00:05:51,210 --> 00:05:52,120
Say what...?!

78
00:05:54,830 --> 00:05:56,630
We're seafaring cooks.

79
00:05:57,170 --> 00:06:00,170
We don't waste even a drop of soup.

80
00:06:12,690 --> 00:06:13,770
– Chef Zeff!
– Chef Zeff!

81
00:06:13,770 --> 00:06:15,190
Old fart...!

82
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:20,900
What is this vile scum of a soup?!

83
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:22,650
If we serve something like this,

84
00:06:22,650 --> 00:06:24,820
we'll go out of business!

85
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:27,120
Knock it off, you old fart!

86
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:30,830
Just how is my soup different
from yours?! Tell me!

87
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:32,910
You think this soup
compares to mine?!

88
00:06:35,790 --> 00:06:37,590
Don't flatter yourself!

89
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,510
Chef Zeff punched him...

90
00:06:41,510 --> 00:06:43,130
Instead of kicking him?

91
00:06:43,130 --> 00:06:47,760
It's a billion years too early for you
to lecture me on cooking, little eggplant!

92
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:51,850
I'm a man who has cooked
on seas across the world.

93
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:57,270
Dammit!

94
00:07:07,780 --> 00:07:11,160
This soup is pretty tasty, you know...

95
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,790
We know that.

96
00:07:12,790 --> 00:07:13,410
Huh?

97
00:07:13,410 --> 00:07:17,670
Everyone here knows
what a fantastic cook Sanji is.

98
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:19,710
It's not bad at all.

99
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:22,380
Yeah, this soup is exquisitely made.

100
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:24,130
Boy, that was scary...

101
00:07:24,130 --> 00:07:25,880
He seriously snapped.

102
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,130
He sure did.

103
00:07:33,060 --> 00:07:38,150
But that idiot won't listen
unless we go this far...

104
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:41,820
Say, kid...

105
00:07:42,190 --> 00:07:45,820
You were saying that you wanted
a cook for your ship, right?

106
00:07:45,820 --> 00:07:49,490
I'm not asking you a favor or anything,

107
00:07:49,490 --> 00:07:52,450
but would you take that
little eggplant with you...

108
00:07:52,990 --> 00:07:54,870
to the Grand Line?

109
00:07:56,330 --> 00:07:58,370
The Grand Line...

110
00:07:58,370 --> 00:08:00,380
is his dream.

111
00:08:02,340 --> 00:08:05,920
Chef Zeff, you made us
put on a hell of a show.

112
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:10,180
I thought for sure he'd figure it out
because of your bad acting.

113
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:13,390
You were the bad actor here.

114
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:14,890
I'll have another bowl!

115
00:08:14,890 --> 00:08:17,060
– Me, too!
– Me, too!

116
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:35,790
I can hear everything,
you damn idiots...

117
00:08:37,580 --> 00:08:39,330
So what do you say, kid?

118
00:08:39,790 --> 00:08:40,750
No.

119
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:41,630
– What?!
– What?!

120
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:46,340
I thought you wanted
a cook for your ship.

121
00:08:47,420 --> 00:08:51,010
Or are you saying that
he's not good enough for you?

122
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:56,020
It's not that he isn't good enough.
I really do want him to come with me.

123
00:08:56,640 --> 00:09:00,140
But he says that he wants to
keep working here as a cook.

124
00:09:00,140 --> 00:09:03,650
Even if you guys ask me
to take him, I can't.

125
00:09:04,270 --> 00:09:09,030
So you're saying that you can't agree
to it until he tells you so himself, huh?

126
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,820
Exactly. More, please!

127
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:13,450
Well... fair enough.

128
00:09:13,990 --> 00:09:15,830
But who knows if that screwed-up
brat can just say that he'll go...

129
00:09:15,830 --> 00:09:19,120
But who knows if that screwed-up
brat can just say that he'll go...

130
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:23,080
I wouldn't hold your breath
for a stubborn idiot like that.

131
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,290
More, please!

132
00:09:52,950 --> 00:09:53,740
Dammit...!

133
00:09:53,740 --> 00:09:54,570
Sanji!

134
00:09:54,570 --> 00:09:56,580
What is he? A fishman?

135
00:09:56,580 --> 00:09:59,330
He came from Fishman Island
to try our cuisine?

136
00:09:59,330 --> 00:10:01,540
Idiot! It's a human and a panda shark!

137
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:03,080
What's going on?

138
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:05,040
Oh! It's Yosaku!

139
00:10:05,460 --> 00:10:07,960
Ah... Big Bro Luffy!

140
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:10,340
You're all by yourself?
Where's everyone else?

141
00:10:10,340 --> 00:10:11,420
Did you find Nami?

142
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:21,100
We didn't actually catch up to her...

143
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:25,600
but based on Big Sis Nami's heading,
we could guess her destination.

144
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:28,650
We can bring her back, then.

145
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:30,780
The thing is...

146
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:37,320
if we're right about this, then she's
headed straight for trouble.

147
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:41,900
In any case, we need
your help, Big Bro Luffy.

148
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:43,120
Please come with me!

149
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:47,210
Alright! I don't really get it,
but okay. Let's go!

150
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:56,890
Wait!

151
00:10:57,890 --> 00:11:01,390
We both have foolish dreams.

152
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:09,320
To achieve my goal—
to find the All Blue...

153
00:11:10,270 --> 00:11:11,230
Sanji?

154
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:13,280
Yeah.

155
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:16,740
I'll come along on your journey
to become King of the Pirates!

156
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:17,570
Huh?

157
00:11:19,030 --> 00:11:22,160
I'll be the cook for your ship.

158
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:24,120
Is that okay or not?

159
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:26,080
It's okay!

160
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,460
Alright!

161
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:29,290
Congratulations, Big Bro Luffy!

162
00:11:29,290 --> 00:11:30,130
Yeah!

163
00:11:30,130 --> 00:11:31,550
– Yay! Yay!
– Yay! Yay!

164
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:33,590
– We got a cook! We'll have good food!
– We got a cook! We'll have good food!

165
00:11:34,220 --> 00:11:36,090
That's what's happening, everyone.

166
00:11:34,220 --> 00:11:36,090
Good food! Good food!

167
00:11:37,380 --> 00:11:40,010
Sorry for causing you
all sorts of trouble.

168
00:11:40,890 --> 00:11:42,010
You're pissin' me off...

169
00:11:42,010 --> 00:11:46,020
I wanted to kick you
out of here myself.

170
00:11:46,020 --> 00:11:49,230
And then you casually
decide just like that?

171
00:11:50,270 --> 00:11:54,240
Sorry for making you show off
your crappy acting skills.

172
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,990
You knew?!

173
00:11:55,990 --> 00:11:57,450
I could hear you in there...

174
00:11:57,450 --> 00:11:58,700
You're all so stupid.

175
00:11:58,700 --> 00:11:59,910
We're what...?!

176
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:03,870
So that means you're willing to go
that far to kick me out,

177
00:12:03,870 --> 00:12:05,250
huh, you old fart?!

178
00:12:05,830 --> 00:12:11,090
Why do you always talk like
such a disrespectful turd?!

179
00:12:12,590 --> 00:12:14,920
That's right, little eggplant!

180
00:12:15,590 --> 00:12:18,090
I couldn't care less for kids, anyway!

181
00:12:18,090 --> 00:12:23,350
Not a single day went by where I didn't
regret letting such a useless brat live.

182
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:26,480
That makes this easier, you old fart!

183
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:29,310
Savor the rest of
your life to the fullest!

184
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:32,940
Is it okay for us to use
such a nice ship?

185
00:12:32,940 --> 00:12:35,150
Of course! It's Sanji's boat.

186
00:12:35,650 --> 00:12:37,990
You still need more?!

187
00:12:37,990 --> 00:12:39,660
Yeah. Give me more meat.

188
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:42,530
Just how many days
will you be at sea?

189
00:12:42,530 --> 00:12:43,620
Don't know...

190
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:49,710
Whoa!

191
00:12:49,710 --> 00:12:53,290
Old fart, is this the Sea Restaurant?

192
00:13:14,020 --> 00:13:16,570
For example, Sanji...

193
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:18,570
Yeah?

194
00:13:19,070 --> 00:13:23,530
Be they master criminals
or escaped convicts,

195
00:13:23,530 --> 00:13:30,000
if these damn bastards are starving
and find their way to this restaurant,

196
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:34,500
that would give us reason
enough to keep fighting,

197
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:36,750
wouldn't you say?

198
00:13:37,380 --> 00:13:38,460
Yeah!

199
00:13:39,510 --> 00:13:41,880
We're gonna be busy!

200
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:44,760
We'll be fine 'cause I'm here!

201
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:56,400
Ouch...

202
00:13:57,690 --> 00:13:58,820
Honestly...

203
00:14:01,110 --> 00:14:02,820
Thinner peels, little eggplant!

204
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:05,820
That really hurt!

205
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:10,250
When someone's focused on
their cooking, just shut up and watch!

206
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:13,210
What?! Don't get smart
with me, you little eggplant!

207
00:14:13,210 --> 00:14:15,380
I'm not a little eggplant!

208
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:18,710
You old fart!

209
00:14:20,170 --> 00:14:21,800
Try this.

210
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:23,800
Did you make it by yourself?

211
00:14:24,390 --> 00:14:25,300
Yeah.

212
00:14:27,350 --> 00:14:28,180
How is it?

213
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:29,720
Disgusting!

214
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:31,680
This is inedible, you little eggplant!

215
00:14:32,390 --> 00:14:34,900
You old fart!

216
00:14:44,570 --> 00:14:46,990
Big Bro Cook sure is taking his time...

217
00:14:46,990 --> 00:14:47,830
Yeah...

218
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,500
This is a long time coming!

219
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:00,960
Get ready, Sanji!

220
00:15:07,930 --> 00:15:10,310
You guys will never kick his ass.

221
00:15:24,070 --> 00:15:25,400
Let's go.

222
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:27,280
Shouldn't you say goodbye?

223
00:15:27,660 --> 00:15:28,910
It's fine.

224
00:15:28,910 --> 00:15:30,240
Sanji!

225
00:15:30,830 --> 00:15:33,500
Keep your feet dry.

226
00:16:09,910 --> 00:16:12,120
Chef Zeff!

227
00:16:13,620 --> 00:16:17,620
Thank you for every damn thing
you've done for me all these years!

228
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,630
I'll never forget your kindness...

229
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:22,170
for as long as I live!

230
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:44,530
You asshole!

231
00:16:46,530 --> 00:16:49,530
I'll miss you, dammit!

232
00:16:49,530 --> 00:16:51,490
I'm gonna miss you!

233
00:17:05,380 --> 00:17:07,260
I'll miss you!

234
00:17:07,260 --> 00:17:09,510
You're making me cry, dammit!

235
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:18,060
You're all idiots!

236
00:17:19,430 --> 00:17:22,900
Men should part without a word.

237
00:17:25,980 --> 00:17:29,070
Let's go! Set sail!

238
00:17:29,070 --> 00:17:32,820
I'll see you again, you damn bastards!

239
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:50,420
If your conviction is such
that you no longer fear death...

240
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:53,640
you'll surely find...

241
00:17:54,510 --> 00:17:56,430
the All Blue.

242
00:17:59,140 --> 00:18:02,480
Guys, customers are
gonna show up soon!

243
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:05,150
Get to work already!

